reviews.text: Such a lovely place to hang out and just relax. I love this beach. Not too crowded considering the time of the year. Parking was easier than I expected. The sand is kept pretty clean of garbage and there's plenty of space to choose your spot, open the chair or rent one, and lay back to enjoy the ocean. Definitely coming back

By far one of the best beaches in Delray. Beautiful entrance with lots of trees, pavilions, showers and bathrooms. Parking is plentiful and just across the street from the park.

The beach is always clean and has a few garbage cans throughout. There's always lots of space available and you can also rent some beach chairs and shade..

Beautiful public space! Newly rebuilt boardwalk and meeting area! 
Lots of parking...excellent access way to the beach in Delray

We went and stayed for two hours. Seemed just perfect for a day at the beach for locals. It was a pretty busy day, but parking was easy to find. We got there at about 1030. The surf was roaring so we didnt spend that much time in the water. Nearly certain we saw a spinner shark off shore and a Man-o-war in the grassline.

Great beach and park. Very calm and relaxing place, far away from the nonsense of the busy everyday life. It's a great place to renew your energies and do yoga classes, that are held in Wednesdays, Fridays and Saturdays at 4pm during winter time, and Wednesdays and Sundays at 6pm during summer.

If the Morikami Museum and Japanese Garden is not on your bucket list of places to visit in Florida, it should be. The art work is thought provoking and beautiful.  The Japanese garden is beautiful. There are walking trails and exhibitions where you can learn about the Japanese culture and the Japanese families that settled in the area. Everything is beautifully maintained and a great place to bring your family and friends. You can enjoy a nature walk, the cafeteria, the gift shop, or just sit on one of the many donated benches to enjoy the breeze and the beautiful landscape.

Lovely, serene place. For those with walking problems it is a hike to see the entire circle, especially on a hot day. There are, however, plenty of benches and the paths are pretty flat. If you don't have time or the inclination to walk all the way around the loop, head left out of the main building. There is a lovely waterfall right away on the left. On the next major peninsula, there is the original building with a nice history of the founder posted in it. Along with bathrooms and drinking fountains. Watch for iquanas and gold fish (by the old building). And sit a spell in silence and ponder the views or your navel! Small gift shop and usually an art exhibit in the main building. We heard the cafe was quite nice, but arrived too late to try it. Definitely recommend. Wear walking shoes a hat, and bring water and a camera!

Such a beautiful and serene place to spend the day or even a few hours. I took my time going through the gardens and honestly I wish I had the chance to spend more time. Every turn in the path was more beautiful and inspiring than the last. Definitely will come back again with more friends and also by myself

Very nice place at a very reasonable price.   We enjoyed a slow stroll through the gardens. We arrived later in the afternoon,  230-245, closed at 5 pm, we were done about 450 pm.  We were not sure if we were going to have enough time to see everything,  but we did.   Not may flowers were out as we visited after blooming.   Not sure what dates that would be,  but I'm sure it would have been alot more spectacular.  I would recommend this place if your looking to do something quite.

This is a very beautiful place to spend sometime at. It has a calming feel to it. Everyone in our group enjoyed themselves. The older as well as the young. Their restaurant had wonderful dishes for us to try. Next time we have company, we'll make sure to take them there.

First time with my husband for Valentines Day, hostess dress in red at the entrance was very rude , the place was empty and we did have reservations made 3 weeks in advance,,,she made us wait 25 min for no reason pretending she was busy. My husband order oysters for me,at $3.50 each you just only hope because is a good Restaurant,  they will be fresh.
I found them bland, small and not tasty. The day after, we did not leave the bathroom. 
Please if somebody had the same experience come out. I asked my husband to call them and let them know but he is a man of a few words, simply we will not be back.

The food is delicious, had the porterhouse, perfectly seasoned, expertly cooked to perfection, delicious sides.  We were all fans of the brussel sprouts and also the potatoes.  As good as the food is, we'll keep coming back for the incredible service.  The staff are a delight to watch, our waiter was friendly and professional, and just a pleasure to interact with.  Top notch!!
Great food. Expensive!  Very very slow service last two visits.

Very good steakhouse. Service was excellent!!! We asked the waiter if they had any chocolate chip cookies for my 18 month old son and the waiter said no but brought him ice cream. I thought that was very nice. Then about 10 min later the manager brought over a chocolate chip cookie and told us he had went to Starbucks a couple of stores down and bought my son a cookie. This shows the type of service and care they have here. My son was soooo happy. This was my first time here but I will be back. Steaks and sides were great and cooked to perfection

Food was very good but I was shocked when we got home with the leftovers .. look at the photo, we had 2 more containers in total food in 3 massive plastic containers that could have easily fit in 1 small one ... how could someone in the kitchen possibly think this was a good idea!

Food was delicious. I had the salmon with black rice. Crispy on the outside tender and juicy inside. Some of my companions are very picky and asked for adjustments to their orders and all were happy. The crispy plantain appetizer is always a big hit

With so many restaurants in Delray to choose from, this restaurant has stood the test of time! The food is amazing from the sangria to the paella! We have always enjoyed the atmosphere and the servers are attentive and knowledgeable.

Been there half a dozen times over a few years. They have some fun drinks and great food. Interactive waiting staff. Right on Atlantic Ave so you can watch the passer-bys if you sit outside. Lots of seating space so I have never worried about going during peak times. We always were seated right away even without a reservation. NOT CHEAP.

Fresh, well seasoned delicious Cuban dishes. From the simple salad dressing to the well marinated skirt steak, everything was amazing. The mojitos are so tasty. Give yourself a taste. We will definitely be back again!

Our server was Javier. He was a lot of fun and very helpful! We had people who loved seafood, meat and a vegan in our party and he had perfect recommendations for all. The food was really good. Its a blend of Latin and South American dishes. Great experience!

I finally decided to come and eat, after driving by this place over 1000 times. Let me start by saying that the staff was friendly! If you like good old all American burgers, thou got to try theirs. Highly recommended!

Glad to finally stop in.  Love the old fashioned Drive-In feel and the great view of Atlantic Ave and the passersby.  I had the Black and White Malted Milkshake and the Patty Melt Burger and they were both top notch. Try adding some ketchup and the mustard with seeds to the sandwich and it adds another level of depth and flavor that won't disappoint.  One of the best quick bite restaurants I've had the pleasure to try in South Florida. I will most definitely return,  hopefully many times over.

DOC'S WAS DIRTY AND I DISREPAIR !
THE MENU IS SMALL BUT WAS RIGHT
ON POINT ?  THE PRICES ARE *HIGH*
FOR THE ITEMS IT SELLS & SIZE OF THE
PORCHES.  IF I OWNED *DOC'S* I WOULD
MAKE IT AN *INSTITUTION* A PLACE THAT
ALL *DELRAY BEACH* WOULD BE PROUD
OF ! ! ! *DOC'S* NEEDS NEW TABLES - CHAIRS - CERAMIC FLOORS - CEILING FANS
AND THE PATIO AREA COULD BE SPECIAL ?
THE BATHROOMS ARE *HORRIBLE* YOU WOULD NOT THINK THE HEALTH DEPARTMENT WOULD *ALLOW*
I had a gyro. It was better than expected 😊 My friend had onion rings which were super fresh. Not too expensive. Overall grade B+
Not the Doc's from my childhood. Just basic box Icecream. McDonald's is probably a little better. Nice location because of the activity on this corner.
Veggie calzone was delicious and gigantic. Went on Tuesday for half off tall boy domestics and they had a great selection. Staff was friendly and attentive.
Great atmosphere with great service. You can't go wrong with this place. We ordered our food and we got it quick! Great selection of beers too!

We came from Georgia where I first encountered this chain. Over there the pizza was amazing. Simply to die for. And when we moved here I was so excited to see that there was a location near us. We drove from Lafayette to dine here because we loved the locations in Georgia so much. I was so disappointed. More like heartbroken. Our buffalo pizza stopped being made halfway up the pizza leaving a thick piece of crust. Our bbq chicken side was burnt. We asked for no onions on both sides there were onions. The crust was not like the other locations. It was hard. My son got the pretzel bites the only good thing that came to our table. It's what I expected my crust on my pizza to be. Our waitress forgot about us once it got busy. The host was the only reason this place got 2 stars. She was amazing and so friendly with my son. I think it needs to meet the management at other locations. Next time we will wait till I visit my in laws in Georgia. Such a huge let down. And dont tell me about it being burnt because it goes into an oven when 2 completely different locations have the same crust and same quality of food on the opposite sides of Georgia. There's something not right with this location.
A very clean  restaurant. Friendly staff not afraid to smile an say hello. Good food. Overall a pleasant experience
Great Pizza! Good servers with efficient service and decent serving time. Try the House special and the mighty meaty! The spinach dip is great too.

I would recommend this place (Family & Friends)
Here's our experience:

Food came out timely, hot and ready to eat. Service was great and fashionable. I enjoyed a classic cheese pizza. 

Comfortably sits 5 people.

I would give it 5 stars but water wasn't easily accessible
For late night pizza it is pretty good. Too many crazy toppings for my taste. But that's just me. Most people would probably enjoy the variety.
The owner, a funny great guy. Pizza's are aleays fresh and it's a quick late night spot.

This is the Delray Beach pizza paradise right off A1A!  The variety of pizzas that are offered daily is phenomenal.  I have yet to try them all, but have yet to have one that I do not like!  Each slice is almost like ordering your own personal pizza, you will not leave hungry!
Great prices and good food. Fast service too.
Staff is always very friendly and the wait is never bad. One of my absolute favorite places to get Pad Thai! Great experience overall.

reviews.author_name: Uri Rendon Owner, Pure Brokers LLC
reviews.text: I have to first say this place has good pricing, especially for the area. One of the sushi dishes was a bit watery (KC roll) and the liquid caused it to fall apart way too easily while being eaten. But overall the dish still tasted ok, which is why I rated 4/5. Everything else my friend and I had was really good. The dishes could have been laid out a little better but as you can see in my videos, they didn’t look terrible.

We haven't been here in years, maybe 15 but friends like it and wanted to go.

Pleasantly surprised at the selection and quality of food.
I started with the Sunomono ,octopus, conch, krab, masago, scallion & cucumber over seaweed salad, very good. My wife ordered her favorite, Tom Kha Kai ,Thai coconut soup with chicken, mushroom, scallion, and bell pepper. She said it was the best she has ever had.

For mains, i had the Deluxe Sashimi , assortment of raw fish including conch & octopus, Came with either soup or salad. Amazing presentation (see the picture). Nice selection of fresh fish. My wife ordered the K.C Roll ,salmon, krab, cream cheese, avocado asparagus, masago, scallion wrapped in cucumber with ponzu sauce.
She loved it.

Definitely will return.

Good food and good service
Friendly / Manerger so nice and friendly
Once a week. My favorite business lunch stop in Boca. Great food. Nice staff. Get's me in and out guickly knowing my short, late lunch break.

Very good sushi. We were a party of 8. While service was slow, I felt it was worth the wait. Fresh....very fresh sushi. Two in our party opted for the Thai food and were very pleased. I would go back.
Absolutely great food, atmosphere and great area in down down Delray. Some of the best food you will experience in south Fla. Highly Recommended.

Visited from out of town.  Been to many Korean restaurants in different cities and Yama is just ok.  Nothing special.  Prices are too high and to have to pay for side dishes such as kimchee is disappointing.  Service was from the staff was good.
Fresh sushi and very yummy menu. Great service!

Wow .....we did the lunch box and my tummy was full of delicious food.  The miso soup, crunchy fresh salad with ginger dressing, spicy pork, sushi with dipping sauce, crunchy cucumber with a seafood note and fried dumplings with sauce and a drink.  Omg if I could I would eat there every day.  The flavors dance on your tongue ....I will be back!!!!🤗
